Website - Bhuvan Thematic Data Dissemination
Website URL - https://bhuvan-app1.nrsc.gov.in/thematic/thematic/index.php 
Website Content Details -
Bhuvan Thematic is a thematic data dissemination service of the National Remote Sensing Centre (NRSC), an autonomous body under the Department of Space, Government of India. It provides a wide range of thematic data layers on India, including land use land cover, wasteland, geomorphology, urban land use, urban sprawl, erosion, water bodies, salt affected & water logged area, flood hazard, and glacial lakes and water bodies.
Thematic data layers are used to understand the spatial distribution of different features and phenomena on the Earth's surface. They can be used for a variety of purposes, including

Planning and development
Natural resource management
Disaster management
Environmental monitoring
Research
Bhuvan Thematic data layers are available in a variety of formats, including vector, raster, and image. They can be accessed and used through the Bhuvan web portal, or through OGC web services.

Some of the benefits of using Bhuvan Thematic data layers include:

They are free and open access.
They are high-resolution and accurate.
They are updated regularly.
They are available in a variety of formats.
Bhuvan Thematic data layers are a valuable resource for anyone who needs to understand the spatial distribution of different features and phenomena on the Earth's surface.
